snippet.textDisplay:
I always love that MREs are ridiculously nondescript about what to use to prop up your MRE as it's heating.

Shame (tyler?) Didn't pull the fun trick of cutting off one section of the heater for coffee.



Lastly... Army.. Really? I'm pretty sure every branch of the military has some reason to have MREs during some area involving the deployment of troops. I know Army and Air Force do. It'd only make sense for Marines as well. I could see the Navy bringing up some reason for SOMEBODY to have MREs, even though a bunch (if not all) of their boats have galleys for proper meals.
